.TH "ms_sensors_write_heater" 9 "ms_sensors_write_heater" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ms_sensors_write_heater \- Write device heater
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" ms_sensors_write_heater
.BI "(struct ms_ht_dev *dev_data "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_data" 12
pointer to temperature/humidity device data
.IP "buf" 12
pointer to char buffer from user space
.IP "len" 12
length of buf
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will write 1 or 0 value in the device
to enable or disable heater.
This function is used for HTU21 and MS8607 chipsets.
.SH "RETURN"
length of buffer, negative errno otherwise.
